Kenyan Inflation Rate May Peak at 22% on Shilling, Standard Chartered Says

-- B y   S a r a h   M c G r e g o r
-- 
2011-06-22T06:26:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/kenyan-inflation-rate-may-peak-at-22-on-shilling-standard-chartered-says.html
Kenya ’s inflation rate may rise to
at least 22 percent “later this year” if the shilling
continues to depreciate and food and fuel prices remain high,
 Razia Khan , head of Africa research at  Standard Chartered  Bank
Plc, said at a briefing in Nairobi, the capital, today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sarah McGregor in Nairobi at 
